parameters:
Zerachiel: There's no doubt that Effy's
curse belongs to the star-reading god,
Eden.

Zerachiel: While playing the role of the
Orpheus Cult's leader, I was cursing
Effy.

Aries: It is to extract the Seventh
Curse from Lady Effy, isn't it?

Zerachiel: One of the forbidden arts
that grows on souls as nourishment,
spreads toxins, and annihilates all
life...

Zerachiel: With the Seventh Curse, I can
obtain the world.

Lala: First of all, I have a question.
Why does the star-reading god want to
obtain the world?

Aries: ...It's a grudge from a thousand
years ago.
In the primordial era, there were many gods in this world.

After spending a long time, the god came
to a conclusion.

CL: 'The world is too vast for the gods
to live in alone.'

CL: What if we create a new race and
live together? Wouldn't that be fun?

And thus, the two chosen by the Creator
were the twin gods.

CL, the kind-hearted and fortunate
goddess, Michelin.

The twin gods, CL, created various
lives.

The life created by the \c[6]Star-
Reading God Eden\c[0], CL, was a high-
level organism...

They are beings such as angel,
dragonkin, giant, and divine beasts.

On the other hand, \CL they possess
overwhelming lifespan and power\CL , but
their reproductive ability is very low.

Because they have the bloodline of
Eden, they are called the \c[6]people of
Eden\c[0].

The life created by the divine magician
Michelin is a multitude of races...

Humans, beastmen, mermaids, elves, and
dwarves are famous.

Compared to the people of Eden, they
are beings with inferior power, magic,
and even lifespan. They are called the
\c[0]people of Michelin\c[1].

The two races have spent a long time
together, cooperating with each other
without any conflict.

Until that day, a thousand years
ago...

A thousand years ago... a massive
meteorite fell onto this planet.

Even if the gods joined forces, this
planet was supposed to disappear without
a trace due to a massive meteorite that
couldn't be avoided.

However, a hero appeared who twisted
that fate.

The hero king who created the later
empire, the \c[0]founder emperor\c[1] of
the \c[6]people of Michelin\c[0].

He used forbidden magic to protect this
planet.

Using the continent where the
\c[6]people of Eden\c[0], who possess
high magical power, live as a catalyst,
they activate a large-scale ritual...

The meteorite fell into a different
world from this planet...

The \c[0]people of Michelin\c[1]
succeeded in surviving by isolating
themselves in the \c[0]other side
world\c[1].

Having lost their hometown, their
comrades, and betrayed by the
\c[1]people of Michelin\c[0]...
How much despair did they feel?

The \c[6]people of Eden\c[0] are
considering revenge.
That's why they are preparing like this.
Lala: You guys sure know a lot...

Zerachiel: ...You didn't learn it since
you were a child? I'm surprised that
Lala doesn't know about it.

Lala: Ah, I'm not interested in history
at all!!

Zerachiel: I never expected Aries to be
the daughter of the Demon King.

Lala: You don't seem like a demon at
all.

Aries: My mother is a beast person, and
that blood runs thick in me.

Zerachiel: I was helped by an incredible
person, huh.
Zerachiel: Well then, shall we go soon?

Lala: We're heading to the Castle of
Vaal, right?

Zerachiel: Yeah, that's where we'll have
our final meeting.

Aries: A joint military invasion by the
Demon King's army and the members of the
cult...

Aries: We will attack the Transference
Gate \c[6]Absorb Gate\c[0] and
infiltrate the other side of the
world...

Aries: I will rescue Lady Effy from the
Seventh Curse.

Lala: Angels may have high physical
abilities, but their numbers are few.

Zerachiel: They will surely bring in a
large number of homunculi, won't they?

Zerachiel: In other words, this is our
chance to board when our forces are not
fully prepared.

Aries: Zerachiel-sama, please take this
with you.

Aries: This is something I received from
Lady Effy.

Aries: I want you to give it to
Zerachiel-sama.
Zerachiel: I will gratefully accept it.
Aries: And this is from me.

Aries: I have infused my magical power
into it. It will surely be of use to
you.

Zerachiel: Aries, I've been indebted to
you for everything.

Zerachiel: Thank you. I'll express my
gratitude in advance.

Aries: It's still too early to say thank
you.

Lala: Hehe, yes. Let's celebrate when
everything is over.
Lala: You really became a dog, huh?

Marnagarm: The Demon Lord and the other
comrades are already waiting at Vaal's
castle.

Aries: Marnagarm, I heard that you
transferred my father to Logres...

Marnagarm: ...No need for thanks. I
can't just hand over the Seventh Curse
to the Star God.
Lala: You're really not obedient at all.

Marnagarm: When you're ready, speak to
me. We'll teleport to Vaal's castle.

Zerachiel: (Let's make sure we're fully
prepared and head to the castle)

Zerachiel: We need to find Aries. I
think she might be indoors.
